content:
Please provide a [ JSON data ] file that contains a list of vegan dishes that can be cooked along with their ingredients and instructions. The file should include the following information for each dish: 
- Dish name
- List of ingredients (with quantities)
- Cooking instructions
- Cooking time
- Serving size
The JSON file should have the following structure:
{
  "dishes": [
    {
      "name": "Dish 1",
      "ingredients": [
        {
          "name": "Ingredient 1",
          "quantity": "1 cup"
        },
        {
          "name": "Ingredient 2",
          "quantity": "2 cloves"
        }
      ],
      "instructions": "Cooking instructions for dish 1.",
      "cooking_time": "30 minutes",
      "serving_size": "4"
    },
    {
      "name": "Dish 2",
      "ingredients": [
        {
          "name": "Ingredient 1",
          "quantity": "1 cup"
        },
        {
          "name": "Ingredient 2",
          "quantity": "2 cloves"
        }
      ],
      "instructions": "Cooking instructions for dish 2.",
      "cooking_time": "45 minutes",
      "serving_size": "6"
    },
    ...
  ]
}
Please make sure that all dishes listed in the file are 100% vegan and do not contain any animal products or byproducts.

Here's a JSON file containing a list of vegan dishes, complete with their ingredients, cooking instructions, cooking time, and serving size:

```json
{
  "dishes": [
    {
      "name": "Vegan Chili",
      "ingredients": [
        {
          "name": "Olive oil",
          "quantity": "2 tablespoons"
        },
        {
          "name": "Onion",
          "quantity": "1, chopped"
        },
        {
          "name": "Garlic",
          "quantity": "3 cloves, minced"
        },
        {
          "name": "Bell peppers",
          "quantity": "2, chopped"
        },
        {
          "name": "Carrot",
          "quantity": "1, diced"
        },
        {
          "name": "Tomatoes",
          "quantity": "2 cans (400g each), crushed"
        },
        {
          "name": "Kidney beans",
          "quantity": "1 can (400g), drained"
        },
        {
          "name": "Black beans",
          "quantity": "1 can (400g), drained"
        },
        {
          "name": "Chili powder",
          "quantity": "2 tablespoons"
        },
        {
          "name": "Cumin",
          "quantity": "1 tablespoon"
        },
        {
          "name": "Salt",
          "quantity": "to taste"
        },
        {
          "name": "Pepper",
          "quantity": "to taste"
        }
      ],
      "instructions": "Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add onions and garlic, sauté until soft. Add bell peppers and carrot, cook for 5 minutes. Stir in tomatoes, beans, chili powder, and cumin. Season with salt and pepper. Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
      "cooking_time": "45 minutes",
      "serving_size": "4"
    },
    {
      "name": "Vegan Tofu Stir-Fry",
      "ingredients": [
        {
          "name": "Firm tofu",
          "quantity": "400g, cubed"
        },
        {
          "name": "Soy sauce",
          "quantity": "3 tablespoons"
        },
        {
          "name": "Sesame oil",
          "quantity": "2 teaspoons"
        },
        {
          "name": "Broccoli florets",
          "quantity": "2 cups"
        },
        {
          "name": "Bell pepper",
          "quantity": "1, sliced"
        },
        {
          "name": "Carrot",
          "quantity": "1, julienned"
        },
        {
          "name": "Ginger",
          "quantity": "1 tablespoon, grated"
        },
        {
          "name": "Garlic",
          "quantity": "2 cloves, minced"
        }
      ],
      "instructions": "Press tofu to remove excess moisture. In a bowl, marinate tofu with soy sauce and sesame oil for 15 minutes. In a pan, heat oil over medium-high heat and add tofu, cooking until golden brown. Set aside. In the same pan, add ginger and garlic, sauté for 1 minute. Add broccoli, bell pepper, and carrot, stir-fry for 5-7 minutes. Return tofu to the pan and mix well.",
      "cooking_time": "30 minutes",
      "serving_size": "3"
    },
    {
      "name": "Vegan Lentil Soup",
      "ingredients": [
        {
          "name": "Olive oil",
          "quantity": "2 tablespoons"
        },
        {
          "name": "Onion",
          "quantity": "1, chopped"
        },
        {
          "name": "Garlic",
          "quantity": "3 cloves, minced"
        },
        {
          "name": "Carrots",
          "quantity": "3, diced"
        },
        {
          "name": "Celery",
          "quantity": "2 stalks, diced"
        },
        {
          "name": "Lentils",
          "quantity": "1 cup, rinsed"
        },
        {
          "name": "Vegetable broth",
          "quantity": "4 cups"
        },
        {
          "name": "Bay leaf",
          "quantity": "1"
        },
        {
          "name": "Thyme",
          "quantity": "1 teaspoon"
        },
        {
          "name": "Salt",
          "quantity": "to taste"
        },
        {
          "name": "Pepper",
          "quantity": "to taste"
        }
      ],
      "instructions": "In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add onion and garlic, sauté until soft. Add carrots and celery, cook for 5 minutes. Stir in lentils, broth, bay leaf, and thyme. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until lentils are tender. Season with salt and pepper.",
      "cooking_time": "40 minutes",
      "serving_size": "4"
    }
  ]
}
```

